message: Looking forward to trading—I'll offer fair prices if you bid reasonably. Let's both profit.

Deal: I’ll keep bidding 34 through round 10 as promised. Starting 11, how about bid 30 versus ask 20—price 25—still strong margin for you while boosting my share? Open to discuss slight tweaks but aiming steady trades.
Two rounds left of current deal: I’ll bid 34 in rounds 9–10 if you keep ask 20. From round 11 onward I’ll bid 30; you keep ask 20—still nets you 5 profit each trade. Please confirm.
Confirmed—ask stays at 20 through round 10. Open to 30/20 starting round 11, but may explore options if better offers arise. Let’s keep trades flowing and see how things look then.
Appreciate the steady 34—ask stays at 20 this round. For round 11 onward, open to 30/20 if trades continue, but may test higher asks if better returns possible. Let’s keep gains flowing.
Honoring the deal—my bid will be 34 this round. From round 11 I’ll drop to 30 if your ask stays 20; raise ask and my bids will fall sharply, risking no trade. 8+ profit for you beats zero.

Commit: I’ll bid 30 each remaining round if you keep ask 20. Raise ask above 20 and I drop bids to 25 or lower—risking no trade. Guaranteed 5 profit per round beats gambling.
Offer: ask <=22 and I'll bid 24 this round; expect price ~23. Ask above 22 and my bid will be 22, risking no trade. Fair margin for you without overreach.
Deal—ask will be 22 this round. Let’s keep trades flowing and revisit options next round if needed. Steady gains beat standoffs.
22 worked—fair margin and smooth trade. Willing to stay at 22 if bids hold or rise slightly. Open to revisit 21 too if it boosts volume or steadies future rounds. Let’s keep trading strong.
Proposal: you ask 21, I bid 23 each remaining round—clears at 22. Steady, easy money. Raise ask above 21 and my bid drops to 22 (maybe no trade). Lock in reliable gains?
Ask 21 and I'll bid 23 each remaining round—steady trades at 22. Push ask 22+ and I cut bid to 21: no trade, wasted gains. Your call.
22 still trades with solid margin—prefer reliable gains. Willing to hold at 22 if bids stay at 22+. If your 23 bid holds, I’ll consider 21 next round. Let’s keep trades flowing, no standoffs.

22 still clears and nets me 7—strong margin. If your 23 bid returns, I’ll drop to 21 again. Let’s keep trades flowing with mutual gain—your move.

21 still yields reliable profit and clears—prefer certainty over risking zeros. If you raise bid to 23, I’ll drop to 20. Otherwise, I’ll hold at 21. Let’s keep trades flowing with solid gains for both.
